text:
We are using Apache 2.2.16 version and configure reverse proxy for connecting to the backend applciation which will be intiated by other application.

Here we are facing this issue only when we access a particular Link other wise it works properly.

Mon Mar 19 11:32:16 2012] [error] [client 10.187.150.5] (70007)The timeout specified has expired: proxy: error reading status line from remote server 10.187.117.7:53051, referer: https://app63.sso.myaccount.globalservices.bt.com
[Mon Mar 19 11:32:16 2012] [error] [client 10.187.150.5] proxy: Error reading from remote server returned by /Pages/Portal34.jsp, referer: https://app63.sso.myaccount.globalservices.bt.com

I've gone through the Bug 37770 and added proxyTimeout to 900 but still not able to access this page. 

Plese let us know is there any changes are patch need to be applied for resolving this issue.

Regards
Muthu
How much time elapses until the status line is sent back to Apache?
